Query 13 — Alternative spaces when usual room is blocked
--student-name: Cao Quang Hung
--target-user: student
================================================================================

SQL logic review:
  ✓ DECLARE parameters: @student_email (NVARCHAR), @blocked_statuses (VARCHAR)
  ✓ CTE usual_space: TOP 1 most-booked space by student (aggregate COUNT on bookings)
  ✓ CTE alternatives: TOP 3 available spaces, same building+floor,
    capacity >= usual space's capacity, excluding the usual space itself
  ✓ Branch 1 (empty history): returns error message if student has 0 bookings
  ✓ Branch 2 (available): returns 1 row with "Your usual space — available"
  ✓ Branch 3 (blocked + alternatives): returns up to 3 alternatives with capacity reason
  ✓ Branch 4 (blocked + no alternatives): returns fallback message
  ✓ Branches are mutually exclusive — only one fires per scenario
  ✓ Uses STRING_SPLIT for @blocked_statuses parameter (SQL Server 2016+)
  ✓ Respects is_deleted = 0 on bookings
  ✓ Uses CTEs and explicit JOINs (no implicit comma joins)
  ✓ Enum values match docs/tech-stack.md

Expected results with default params (Alice Johnson):
  - Branch 2 fires: CL-201 (available) → 1 row, "Your usual space — available"
  - Non-zero result guaranteed ✅

Expected results if testing with MTG-001 as usual space (under_maintenance):
  - Branch 3 fires: AUD-101 (cap 200 ≥ 10) → 1 row, "Alternative #1"
  - Non-zero result guaranteed ✅
